      • replaceBinary

        public String replaceBinary(Binary binary)
        Replace the data of the binary in the CoT. This will result in a new ID for the binary. The old ID will stop existing.
        Parameters:
        binary - the Binary that has the (old) ID and the (new) data. The ID will be updated.
        Returns:
        the new ID of the binary.

      • getData

        public byte[] getData(Binary binary)
        Get (or "fill in") the actual binary data into a Binary (e.g. from a BinariesCollection). This data is identified by the ID of the Binary (and not the self-link (although that would probably work too)).
        Parameters:
        binary - the Binary for which the data shall be downloaded. Will be enriched with that data.
        Returns:
        the original byte[] from the response or null, if the body is empty.
